%global packname  ggsignif
%global packver   0.6.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.6.0
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Significance Brackets for 'ggplot2'

License:          GPL-3
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-ggplot2 >= 2.0.0
Requires:         R-CRAN-ggplot2 >= 2.0.0

%description
Enrich your 'ggplots' with group-wise comparisons. This package provides
an easy way to indicate if two groups are significantly different.
Commonly this is shown by a bracket on top connecting the groups of
interest which itself is annotated with the level of significance (NS, *,
**, ***). The package provides a single layer (geom_signif()) that takes
the groups for comparison and the test (t.test(), wilcox.text() etc.) as
arguments and adds the annotation to the plot.

